input.prompt:
Design the implementation plan for enhancing the BIT Dropdown Button Elementor widget (v3.0.0 → v3.1.0) in a WordPress mu-plugin.

## Current File
`/Users/dcambria/scripts/server-tools/v2/docker-dev/sites/concertacao/wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-dropdown-btn.php` (419 lines, v3.0.0)

Current render() generates:
```html
<div class="dropdown-btn-wrapper">
  <div class="dropdown-btn-container">
    <button class="dropdown-btn-toggle" type="button">
      <div class="dropdown-btn-content">
        <span class="dropdown-btn-label">DOWNLOAD</span>
        <span class="dropdown-btn-icon"><!-- SVG or FA icon --></span>
      </div>
    </button>
    <div class="dropdown-btn-menu">
      <a href="/?jet_download=HASH" rel="nofollow noopener">Português</a>
      <a href="/?jet_download=HASH" rel="nofollow noopener">English</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Requirements to Implement

### 1. Fix MEDIA control to accept PDF/DOCX/ZIP
Current `item_file` MEDIA control has no `media_types` specified, defaults to `['image']`, shows "Escolher imagem" button.  
Fix: Set `'media_types' => ['image', 'application/pdf', 'application/zip', 'application/msword', 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document']` on the `item_file` control. Update description text to "PDF, DOCX, ZIP ou imagem. Link criptografado via JetElements."

### 2. Single item = direct download (no dropdown)
When the repeater has exactly 1 valid link, render as a direct `<a>` anchor (not button+dropdown). Same visual appearance, no hover dropdown. The anchor should have the direct download href and `rel="nofollow noopener"`.  
HTML for single mode:
```html
<div class="dropdown-btn-wrapper">
  <div class="dropdown-btn-container">
    <a class="dropdown-btn-toggle dropdown-btn-single" href="..." rel="nofollow noopener">
      <div class="dropdown-btn-content">
        <span class="dropdown-btn-label">DOWNLOAD</span>
        <span class="dropdown-btn-file-size">3.2 MB</span>  <!-- if file_size filled -->
        <span class="dropdown-btn-icon">...</span>
      </div>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
```

### 3. WPML compatibility
Elementor + WPML Multilingual plugin handles translation of TEXT, MEDIA, URL, REPEATER controls automatically. No special code needed. The widget is already WPML-compatible as-is with standard controls. Just document this.

### 4. JetEngine meta repeater field support
Add a "data source" feature so the widget can read from a JetEngine meta repeater field (for use in JetEngine Listing Grid) instead of static Elementor data.

Controls to add in Content tab (after current repeater):
```php
// Source selector (shown always)
$this->add_control('data_source', [
    'label' => 'Fonte dos dados',
    'type' => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::SELECT,
    'default' => 'static',
    'options' => ['static' => 'Estático (Elementor)', 'meta_field' => 'Campo meta (JetEngine)'],
]);

// Meta key (shown only when data_source = meta_field)
$this->add_control('meta_key', [
    'label' => 'Nome do campo meta',
    'type' => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::TEXT,
    'condition' => ['data_source' => 'meta_field'],
    // e.g. 'arquivos_download'
]);

// Sub-field key mappings
$this->add_control('meta_key_label', [..., 'default' => 'label', 'condition' => ['data_source' => 'meta_field']]);
$this->add_control('meta_key_file_id', [..., 'default' => 'file_id', 'condition' => ['data_source' => 'meta_field']]);
$this->add_control('meta_key_fallback_url', [..., 'default' => 'fallback_url', 'condition' => ['data_source' => 'meta_field']]);
$this->add_control('meta_key_file_size', [..., 'default' => 'file_size', 'condition' => ['data_source' => 'meta_field']]);
```

Also wrap the existing `links` REPEATER control with `'condition' => ['data_source' => 'static']`.

Render logic for meta field source:
```php
if ( 'meta_field' === $s['data_source'] && ! empty( $s['meta_key'] ) ) {
    $raw = [];
    if ( function_exists('jet_engine') && ! empty( jet_engine()->listings ) && ! empty( jet_engine()->listings->data ) ) {
        $raw = jet_engine()->listings->data->get_meta( $s['meta_key'] );
    }
    if ( empty( $raw ) ) {
        $raw = get_post_meta( get_the_ID(), $s['meta_key'], true );
    }
    if ( is_string( $raw ) ) { $raw = maybe_unserialize( $raw ); }
    $links_raw = is_array( $raw ) ? $raw : [];

    $k_label    = ! empty( $s['meta_key_label'] )        ? $s['meta_key_label']        : 'label';
    $k_file_id  = ! empty( $s['meta_key_file_id'] )      ? $s['meta_key_file_id']      : 'file_id';
    $k_fallback = ! empty( $s['meta_key_fallback_url'] )  ? $s['meta_key_fallback_url'] : 'fallback_url';
    $k_size     = ! empty( $s['meta_key_file_size'] )     ? $s['meta_key_file_size']    : 'file_size';

    foreach ( $links_raw as $row ) {
        $links[] = [
            'item_label'        => $row[ $k_label ]    ?? '',
            'item_file'         => [ 'id' => (int) ( $row[ $k_file_id ] ?? 0 ), 'url' => '' ],
            'item_fallback_url' => [ 'url' => $row[ $k_fallback ] ?? '', 'is_external' => false ],
            'item_file_size'    => $row[ $k_size ] ?? '',
        ];
    }
} else {
    $links = $s['links'] ?? [];
}
```

### 5. File size display
Add `item_file_size` TEXT control to the repeater (always visible, not conditioned):
```php
$repeater->add_control('item_file_size', [
    'label'       => 'Tamanho do arquivo',
    'type'        => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::TEXT,
    'placeholder' => '3.2 MB',
    'ai'          => ['active' => false],
]);
```

Display in HTML:
- In dropdown items: `<a href="..."><span class="dropdown-btn-item-label">Português</span><span class="dropdown-btn-file-size">3.2 MB</span></a>`
- In single-item button: between label and icon (already shown in template above)
- Only render the `<span class="dropdown-btn-file-size">` if `item_file_size` is not empty

Style controls to add in the "Menu Dropdown" section:
```php
$this->add_control('file_size_color', [
    'label' => 'Cor do tamanho',
    'type' => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::COLOR,
    'selectors' => ['{{WRAPPER}} .dropdown-btn-file-size' => 'color: {{VALUE}};'],
]);
```

### CSS additions (bit-dropdown-btn.css)
```css
/* File size label */
.dropdown-btn-container .dropdown-btn-file-size {
    font-size   : 0.75em;
    font-weight : 400;
    text-transform: none;
    opacity     : 0.75;
}

/* Dropdown item layout when file size present */
.dropdown-btn-container .dropdown-btn-menu a {
    display        : flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items    : center;
    gap            : 8px;
}
```

## Files to modify
1. `wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-dropdown-btn.php` (site)
2. `wordpress/wp-content/mu-plugins/bit-dropdown-btn.css` (site)
3. `docker-dev/common/mu-plugins/bit-dropdown-btn.php` (mirror)
4. `docker-dev/common/mu-plugins/bit-dropdown-btn.css` (mirror)

## Version bump
v3.0.0 → v3.1.0

## Output needed
Provide a clear, step-by-step implementation plan covering:
1. Exact code changes for each control addition
2. render() refactor showing the two-pass approach (first build valid_links array, then decide mode)
3. CSS changes
4. Mirror copy steps
5. Verification steps

The plan should be detailed enough that a developer can implement without further clarification.

